[[Image:Maku museum.jpg|thumb|right|''Baqcheh Jooq Palace'' or ''Kakh Muzeh Maku'', is currently a museum.]]'''Baqcheh Jooq Palace''' is a palace located between the border towns of [[Maku, Iran|Maku]] and [[Bazargan, Piranshahr|Bazargan]] in [[West Azarbaijan]].

It is situated in a vast garden covering about {{convert|11|ha}}. This palace was built at the end of [[Qajar dynasty]] under the orders of [[Iqbal-ol-Saltaneh Makui]], one of the commanders of [[Mozaffar al-Din Shah Qajar|Mozafaredin Shah]].

Being located on the main transit road between Turkey and Europe, it is visited by thousand of tourists annually.

