{{orphan|date=February 2018}} {{Infobox building | name = Nakhchivan Buzkhana | native_name={{lang-az| Naxçıvan Buzxanası }} | former_names = | alternate_names = | image = Naxçıvan buzxanası.jpg | caption = | altitude = | building_type = | architectural_style = | location =[[Nakhchivan (city)|Nakhchivan]], [[Nakhchivan Autonomous Republic]], [[Azerbaijan]] {{flagicon|Azerbaijan}} | address = | client = | owner = | current_tenants = | landlord = | coordinates = | start_date = | completion_date = 14th-17th century | inauguration_date = | renovation_date = | architect = | other_designers = | references = }}
'''Nakhchivan Buzkhana''' is an ice-house located in [[Nakhchivan (city)|Nakhchivan]]. It is one of the largest [[Ice house (building)|ice-houses]] in [[Azerbaijan]]. The ice-house is located on the southern side of the city of Nakhchivan, also near the [[Imamzadeh complex in Nakhchivan|Imamzadeh complex]]. There is also another ice-house with similar architectural structure in [[Ordubad]], Azerbaijan.<ref name=" impnakhchivanaz"/> There are different ideas on date of built of the ice-house. Academician A.Salamzadeh and K.Mammadzade proclaims that the buzkhana was built in the beginning of XIV century. But it is also accepted that it was built during the reign of Shah Abbas in the XVII century. According to Arif Azizov, the honored architect of the Autonomous Republic and director of the Nakhchivan Scientific-Restoration Production Department, the ice-houses were built on the banks of the rivers historically. <ref name="anl">{{cite web|title= Naxçıvan buzxanası|url= http://www.anl.az/down/meqale/azerbaycan/azerbaycan_mart2009/71356.htm|publisher= anl.az |language= az|accessdate=8 February 2018}} </ref> ==Design== The monument is in rectangular form. Its length is 20 meters, width is 9 meters, and height is 9.6 meters. A ventilation system was installated. It allowed the use of ice reserves efficiently in summer.<ref name="anl"/> There are six small domes on the roof. Typical features of the Nakhchivan ice-house are natural construction from bricks, the light and dynamic design scheme.<ref name=" impnakhchivanaz"/> The ice was destroyed as a result of intensive erosion. In 2013, it was restored by the instruction of the Chairman of the Supreme Assembly of the [[Nakhchivan Autonomous Republic]].<ref name="impnakhchivanaz"/> ==Usage== In ancient times, local residents used ice-houses to protect themselves and their personal food products against heat in summer.<ref name="impnakhchivanaz">{{cite web|title= Naxçıvan şəhər buzxanası|url= http://imp.nakhchivan.az/index.php/asagi-slayd/89-naxc-van-s-h-r-buzxanas|publisher= imp.nakhchivan.az |language= az|accessdate=8 February 2018}} </ref> Ice was made during winter months. Drinking water of the river was shed into the cellar to make it ice. Usage of straw was protecting melt of the ice.<ref name="naxcivantv">{{cite web|title= Naxçıvan inciləri: Buzxanalar-Fotolar |url= http://naxcivantv.az/index.php/x-b-rl-r/940-buzxana.html|publisher= naxcivantv.az|language= az|accessdate=8 February 2018}} </ref> In the 20th century local residents started using refrigerators in their houses, which decreased the use of ice-houses.{{citation needed|date=February 2018}} ==See also== *[[Ordubad Buzkhana]] *[[Architecture of Azerbaijan]]
